The paper presents a navigation approach for robots in crowded environments, which involves processing LiDAR scans and predicting human velocity. This falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO) and computer vision (cs.CV). The approach also involves training a deep learning model (cs.LG, cs.AI) and ensuring safety in human-robot interaction (cs.SY).
